-- North Korea Threatens `Nuclear Deterrence' as U.S. Plans Naval Exercises
-- Vivek Shankar
-- 2010-07-23T21:14:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/north-korea-threatens-nuclear-deterrence-as-u-s-plans-naval-exercises.html

          
          
             North Korea plans to “legitimately
counter” with nuclear deterrence the joint U.S.-South Korean
naval exercises in the East Sea of Korea, KCNA reported, citing
the country’s National Defence Commission.  
 North Korea described the planned July 25-July 28
activities as the largest-ever nuclear war exercises, according
to KCNA.  
          
          


  


        